gomodel:SYNGO_2881  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: [Fig.2: \"Dynamin-3 Concentrates in Dendritic Spines and Correlates with the Presence of an Endocytic Zone\"]\n\n[Fig.3: \"Dynamin-3 Localizes to Spine Membrane Domains Lateral to the PSD\"]\n\nFig.4: \"A Dyn3-Homer-Shank Protein Complex Couples the EZ and the PSD\"\n\nFig.5: \"Oligomerization of Dynamin-3 is Required to Link the Endocytic Machinery to the PSD\"\n\nFig.6: \"Endogenous Dynamin-3 is Required for Postsynaptic Positioning of the Endocytic Zone\". Experimental description: - \"Hippocampal neuron cultures were prepared from E18 rat embryos ...\"\n- Overexpressed Dynamin-3; DNM3 is of rat species: \"PSD-95-GFP was provided by David Bredt. EGFP tagged dynamin-1aa (Homo sapiens), dynamin-2ab (Rattus norvegicus) and dynamin-3aaa (Rattus norvegicus) were gifts from Mark McNiven\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_2881" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
